<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><language>en</language><title>RFI - All the news from France, Europe, Africa and the rest of the world.</title><description>Follow any political information, cultural, sporting and live streaming on RFI. The latest information, news and events around the world.</description><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/</link><lastBuildDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 17:08:47 GMT</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.rfi.fr/en/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><category>International</category><title>Iran 'weakened but dangerous' as US air defence stocks face strain</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260306-iran-weakened-but-dangerous-as-us-missile-stocks-face-long-war-test</link><description>
Six days into the war between the United States, Israel and Iran, bombardments are intensifying – as are questions about how long the conflict can last, whether air defence systems can keep up and what a victory over Iran would mean. Retired general François Chauvancy spoke to RFI about Iran’s ability to resist and whether the US and its allies can sustain the current pace of the war.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/19fb8df0-18b6-11f1-87d4-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/2026-03-05T132051Z-643071325-RC2RVJA114XZ-RTRMADP-3-IRAN-CRISIS-ISRAEL-MILITARY.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/19fb8df0-18b6-11f1-87d4-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/2026-03-05T132051Z-643071325-RC2RVJA114XZ-RTRMADP-3-IRAN-CRISIS-ISRAEL-MILITARY.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">16be6808-194a-11f1-aea2-45d3b84827fd</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 17:07:55 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/19fb8df0-18b6-11f1-87d4-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/2026-03-05T132051Z-643071325-RC2RVJA114XZ-RTRMADP-3-IRAN-CRISIS-ISRAEL-MILITARY.jpg">© Ilan Rosenberg / Reuters</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>Hungary vows pressure on Ukraine over Druzhba oil pipeline shutdown</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260306-hungary-vows-pressure-on-ukraine-over-druzhba-oil-pipeline-shutdown</link><description>
Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban has pledged to use “political and financial tools” to force Ukraine to restart flows through the Druzhba pipeline, the key route for Russian oil to Hungary and Slovakia. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e493e202-c481-11ec-8bec-005056bf8594/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22115343860674%20%281%29.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e493e202-c481-11ec-8bec-005056bf8594/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22115343860674%20%281%29.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">cda08360-1942-11f1-9b2d-3f309ec812f2</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 15:59:36 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e493e202-c481-11ec-8bec-005056bf8594/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22115343860674%20%281%29.jpg">AP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>France</category><title>France ramps up military aid to Lebanon as Macron calls for halt in attacks</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/france/20260306-france-ramps-up-military-aid-to-lebanon-as-macron-calls-for-halt-in-attacks-middle-east-war</link><description>
France will strengthen its cooperation with the Lebanese Armed Forces and provide armoured transport vehicles along with operational and logistical support, President Emmanuel Macron has said, as Lebanon is pulled deeper into the war in the Middle East.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7a66a5e2-0bc6-11f0-b5f6-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25087358769502.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7a66a5e2-0bc6-11f0-b5f6-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25087358769502.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">bbc5c3a0-192c-11f1-bd75-0f890bfec760</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 08:27:51 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7a66a5e2-0bc6-11f0-b5f6-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25087358769502.jpg">© Sarah Meyssonnier / AP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>France</category><title>France accuses Russia of election interference using fake website</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/france/20260306-france-accuses-russia-of-election-interference-using-fake-website-bournazel</link><description>
French officials have accused a Russian group tied to military intelligence of foreign interference after it sought to discredit a centre-right candidate in upcoming local elections via a fraudulent website.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c71d1094-efcb-11f0-ae2e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-922X79E.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c71d1094-efcb-11f0-ae2e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-922X79E.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">70adc49a-1962-11f1-8ed8-11a85ba3e2dd</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 14:49:50 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c71d1094-efcb-11f0-ae2e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-922X79E.jpg">© AFP - JOEL SAGET, MARTIN BUREAU </source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Africa</category><title>'Bring our sons home': Kenyan families demand action over Russian war recruitment</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/africa/20260306-bring-our-sons-home-kenyan-families-demand-action-over-russian-war-recruitment</link><description>
Families of young Kenyan men who found themselves fighting in Ukraine after being duped into joining the Russian military are calling on the Kenyan government to provide information on their whereabouts – and for a ban on any future recruitment.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c0996fe6-194d-11f1-b22e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/AP26064415003150.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c0996fe6-194d-11f1-b22e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/AP26064415003150.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">2ab59b9e-194d-11f1-9205-45d3b84827fd</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 12:49:50 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/c0996fe6-194d-11f1-b22e-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/AP26064415003150.jpg">AP - Brian Inganga</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Sports</category><title>'King Arthur' leads French hopes at Paralympic Winter Games</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20260306-king-arthur-bauchet-leads-french-hopes-at-paralympic-winter-games</link><description>
Following a record medal haul at last month's Milano-Cortina Winter Olympics, France's para athletes are hoping to replicate this success when the Paralympic Games kick off on Friday.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/b13a679e-18ad-11f1-82c4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072110230406.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/b13a679e-18ad-11f1-82c4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072110230406.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">d742b302-189d-11f1-a8b0-1339bbd62600</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 06:10:01 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/b13a679e-18ad-11f1-82c4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072110230406.jpg">AP - Andy Wong</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Culture</category><title>New Zealand director Peter Jackson to receive honorary Palme d'Or in Cannes</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/culture/20260306-new-zealand-director-peter-jackson-to-receive-honorary-palme-d-or-in-cannes</link><description>
New Zealand filmmaker Peter Jackson is set to receive an honorary Palme d'Or at the Cannes Film Festival this year in recognition of his contribution to cinema. The director of the Lord of the Rings trilogy called it "one of the greatest privileges of my career".
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6a5a1d54-195e-11f1-a754-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/000-1B55NF.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6a5a1d54-195e-11f1-a754-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/000-1B55NF.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">979c1350-1948-11f1-889a-45d3b84827fd</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 13:14:47 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6a5a1d54-195e-11f1-a754-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/000-1B55NF.jpg">© Anthony HARVEY / AFP</source><dc:creator>Ollia Horton with RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>France</category><title>Police officer to face lesser charge over 2023 killing of teenager Nahel</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/france/20260306-police-officer-to-face-lesser-charge-over-2023-killing-of-teenager-nahel</link><description>
A French policeman who shot and killed a teenager at point-blank range during a traffic stop in the working-class suburbs north of Paris – sparking a week of violent protests nationwide – will stand trial for "violence resulting in death" rather than murder.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/32d4cee4-18b7-11f1-bca3-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Screenshot-2026-03-05-at-17-59-41-Mort-de-Nahel-ce-que-r%C3%A9v%C3%A8lent-les-premiers-%C3%A9l%C3%A9ments-de-l-enqu%C3%AAte-France-24.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/32d4cee4-18b7-11f1-bca3-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Screenshot-2026-03-05-at-17-59-41-Mort-de-Nahel-ce-que-r%C3%A9v%C3%A8lent-les-premiers-%C3%A9l%C3%A9ments-de-l-enqu%C3%AAte-France-24.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">12ccbe22-1943-11f1-b978-9393ccb78e02</guid><pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:07:08 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/32d4cee4-18b7-11f1-bca3-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Screenshot-2026-03-05-at-17-59-41-Mort-de-Nahel-ce-que-r%C3%A9v%C3%A8lent-les-premiers-%C3%A9l%C3%A9ments-de-l-enqu%C3%AAte-France-24.png">© Ohana_FNG/AP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>France lets US planes use its bases for non-combat missions in Iran</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260305-france-confirms-us-aircraft-temporarily-using-its-bases-for-iran-bombing-missions</link><description>
France on Thursday confirmed it had temporarily allowed the US Air Force to use one of its bases for missions in Iran. The French military says it has guarantees that only planes not involved in carrying out strikes will land at the country's facilities.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6ae77f30-c52d-11eb-9f74-005056bf87d6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP235054343588.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6ae77f30-c52d-11eb-9f74-005056bf87d6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP235054343588.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">30084a06-1899-11f1-8dfe-c77057ec42f3</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 16:22:54 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6ae77f30-c52d-11eb-9f74-005056bf87d6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP235054343588.jpg">© AP - Claude Paris </source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>French officials meet fuel suppliers as Iran conflict lifts oil prices</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260305-french-finance-chiefs-try-to-allay-fears-of-big-spike-in-petrol-pump-prices</link><description>
French finance chiefs on Thursday moved to calm fears of a sharp rise in fuel prices as fighting between Israel and Iran in the Middle East entered a sixth day and global oil prices climbed.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6631ade0-f619-11f0-a39b-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25344714722775.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6631ade0-f619-11f0-a39b-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25344714722775.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">22d4bdae-1873-11f1-b797-6de48581e15b</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 10:19:44 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/6631ade0-f619-11f0-a39b-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25344714722775.jpg">© AP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Sports</category><title>Boycott over Russian inclusion overshadows Paralympics opening</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20260305-boycott-overshadows-launch-of-milano-cortina-winter-paralympics</link><description>
Several countries have announced they will boycott the opening ceremony of the Milano-Cortina Winter Paralympic Games on Friday, in protest at the organisers' move to allow para athletes from Russia and its close ally Belarus to compete under their national flags.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/58b8ca8a-0cdb-11f1-abb0-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072472331958.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/58b8ca8a-0cdb-11f1-abb0-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072472331958.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">1f9f0304-17b2-11f1-9ed7-19abe0794231</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 14:14:37 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/58b8ca8a-0cdb-11f1-abb0-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/AP22072472331958.jpg">© Dita Alangkara / AP</source><dc:creator>Paul Myers</dc:creator></item><item><category>France</category><title>MSF files defamation complaint against British far-right group</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/france/20260305-msf-files-defamation-complaint-against-british-far-right-group</link><description>
Aid group Médecins Sans Frontières (Doctors Without Borders, or MSF) has filed a complaint for defamation against a British far-right group after one of its teams was verbally attacked in northern France last year while returning from an assignment to assist migrants.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2ef13670-f132-11f0-85ad-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/000-64CG3KF.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2ef13670-f132-11f0-85ad-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/000-64CG3KF.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">d43eabd6-1887-11f1-be7d-c378130c6eaa</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 14:12:20 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2ef13670-f132-11f0-85ad-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/000-64CG3KF.jpg">AFP - SAMEER AL-DOUMY</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>Military bases and trade routes leave Africa exposed to war fallout</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260305-military-bases-and-trade-routes-leave-africa-exposed-to-war-fallout</link><description>
Africa hosts military bases within reach of Iranian missiles and is feeling the impact of rising oil prices and threats to shipping, as the continent again suffers from events largely beyond its control.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/50b13ca8-1872-11f1-8879-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/berbera-afp-000-98AY84R.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/50b13ca8-1872-11f1-8879-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/berbera-afp-000-98AY84R.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">4a7309fe-1866-11f1-9dac-6143071a2a47</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 07:38:23 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/50b13ca8-1872-11f1-8879-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/berbera-afp-000-98AY84R.jpg">AFP - TONY KARUMBA</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Africa</category><title>Landslide at DR Congo coltan mine kills more than 200, including children</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/africa/20260305-landslide-at-eastern-dr-congo-coltan-mine-kills-200-children-rubaya</link><description>
More than 200 people were killed on Tuesday in a landslide triggered by heavy rains at the Rubaya coltan mine in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, the country's mining ministry said late Wednesday.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/cc7b231e-187a-11f1-a941-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/rubaya-afp-after-the-landslide-4march2026-000-94TB4UZ.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/cc7b231e-187a-11f1-a941-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/rubaya-afp-after-the-landslide-4march2026-000-94TB4UZ.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">cfb955d4-1878-11f1-9318-e1c1abf28dbd</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 11:28:32 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/cc7b231e-187a-11f1-a941-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/rubaya-afp-after-the-landslide-4march2026-000-94TB4UZ.jpg">© AFP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>Ukrainian refugees face uncertain future as Poland scraps special status</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260305-ukrainian-refugees-face-uncertain-future-as-poland-scraps-special-status</link><description>
Poland is ending the special status that gave Ukrainian refugees equal access to the labour market, social benefits and healthcare. The system expires on Thursday, meaning many will now face stricter rules to work or receive support.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7ecef570-0441-11f1-a613-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Kajetan-Wro%CC%81blewski-conseille-aux-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-Ukrainiens-qu-il-acceuille-de-continuer-leur-pe%CC%81riple-jusqu-en-Finalnde-au-Danemark-ou-en-Norve%CC%80ge-ou%CC%80-les-conditions-d-accueil-des-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-sont-meilleures-qu.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7ecef570-0441-11f1-a613-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Kajetan-Wro%CC%81blewski-conseille-aux-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-Ukrainiens-qu-il-acceuille-de-continuer-leur-pe%CC%81riple-jusqu-en-Finalnde-au-Danemark-ou-en-Norve%CC%80ge-ou%CC%80-les-conditions-d-accueil-des-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-sont-meilleures-qu.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a762a9fc-17bd-11f1-b6d1-7fea521ce5b8</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 07:01:32 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/7ecef570-0441-11f1-a613-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Kajetan-Wro%CC%81blewski-conseille-aux-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-Ukrainiens-qu-il-acceuille-de-continuer-leur-pe%CC%81riple-jusqu-en-Finalnde-au-Danemark-ou-en-Norve%CC%80ge-ou%CC%80-les-conditions-d-accueil-des-re%CC%81fugie%CC%81s-sont-meilleures-qu.jpg">© RFI / Adrien Sarlat</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>Spain denies US claim of military cooperation on Iran as rift deepens</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260305-spain-denies-united-states-claim-military-cooperation-iran-war-deepening-rift</link><description>
Spain has doubled down on its opposition to Washington's use of its bases against Iran, after US President Donald Trump's threats of trade reprisals over the spat deepened a rift between the NATO allies.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2cf85fa8-17b9-11f1-93c0-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99VJ79E.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2cf85fa8-17b9-11f1-93c0-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99VJ79E.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a15a3500-1878-11f1-9625-6de48581e15b</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 10:06:43 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/2cf85fa8-17b9-11f1-93c0-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99VJ79E.jpg">AFP - THOMAS COEX,ANDREW CABALLERO-REYNOLDS</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Sports</category><title>Toulouse shock Marseille and Nice oust Lorient to reach Coupe de France semis</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20260305-toulouse-shock-marseille-and-nice-oust-lorient-to-reach-coupe-de-france-semis</link><description>
Toulouse and Nice will feature in the hat on Thursday for the draw for the semifinals of the Coupe de France following penalty shootout wins over Marseille and Lorient respectively.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/4fbbf372-186a-11f1-8c99-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/coupe-de-france.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/4fbbf372-186a-11f1-8c99-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/coupe-de-france.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">b21be438-1869-11f1-9dd6-198916460ab0</guid><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 08:15:25 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/4fbbf372-186a-11f1-8c99-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/coupe-de-france.jpg">© AFP - FRANCK FIFE </source><dc:creator>Paul Myers</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>EU unveils 'Made in Europe' rules in bid to stem industrial decline</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260304-eu-unveils-made-in-europe-rules-in-bid-to-stem-industrial-decline</link><description>
The European Union has unveiled new “Made in Europe” regulations to help bolster its manufacturers in the face of competition, including from China. While the bloc’s industry chief has heralded the move as a major shift in economic doctrine, it risks fuelling criticism from Beijing over perceived protectionism.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e7baeb10-f4da-11ef-a876-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25034521576869.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e7baeb10-f4da-11ef-a876-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25034521576869.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">7cecb418-17ba-11f1-ac23-c583358e3807</guid><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 16:21:53 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/e7baeb10-f4da-11ef-a876-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/AP25034521576869.jpg">© Martin Meissner/AP</source><dc:creator>Jan van der Made</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>French jets intercept Iranian drones as first evacuees arrive in Paris</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260304-first-flight-repatriating-french-nationals-from-middle-east-arrives-in-paris-oman-iran-war</link><description>
French authorities said Rafale fighter jets have neutralised Iranian drones targeting the United Arab Emirates, as the widening Middle East war also forced France to bring citizens home. A first repatriation flight carrying French nationals stranded in the region landed in Paris early on Wednesday, with more evacuations planned.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/fbc2f9ac-17db-11f1-a926-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99QN8WB.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/fbc2f9ac-17db-11f1-a926-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99QN8WB.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">23ff8daa-179f-11f1-b6ba-ebc8bf0b5d26</guid><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 08:22:24 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/fbc2f9ac-17db-11f1-a926-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/000-99QN8WB.jpg">© AFP - STEPHANE DE SAKUTIN</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>International</category><title>UK halts study visas from four countries to stop students claiming asylum</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20260304-uk-halts-study-visas-from-afghanistan-cameroon-myanmar-sudan-to-stop-students-claiming-asylum</link><description>
The British government has imposed an "emergency brake" on visas for students from Afghanistan, Cameroon, Myanmar and Sudan, in response to what it said was a surge of requests for asylum from people arriving in the United Kingdom to study.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8dcb2e4e-17c0-11f1-bf0f-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-36GE98F.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8dcb2e4e-17c0-11f1-bf0f-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-36GE98F.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">b36aee4e-17ae-11f1-85d2-a55124ae4ea6</guid><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 13:36:06 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8dcb2e4e-17c0-11f1-bf0f-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/000-36GE98F.jpg">© Andy Buchanan / AFP</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>France</category><title>French police arrest two more suspects over killing of far-right activist</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/france/20260304-french-police-arrest-two-more-suspects-over-killing-of-far-right-activist</link><description>
Two more men were arrested on Wednesday morning in connection with the death of far-right activist Quentin Deranque in Lyon on 12 February.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/93768b90-0f28-11f1-8756-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Affiche-d-hommage-%C3%A0-Quentin-Deranque.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/93768b90-0f28-11f1-8756-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Affiche-d-hommage-%C3%A0-Quentin-Deranque.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a26371a2-17b3-11f1-9d2b-19abe0794231</guid><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 11:54:59 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/93768b90-0f28-11f1-8756-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/Affiche-d-hommage-%C3%A0-Quentin-Deranque.jpg">AFP - SAMEER AL-DOUMY</source><dc:creator>RFI</dc:creator></item><item><category>Sports</category><title>French star Wembanyama muscles another NBA prize into growing collection</title><link>https://www.rfi.fr/en/sports/20260304-french-star-wembanyama-muscles-another-nba-prize-into-growing-collection</link><description>
French basketball star Victor Wembanyama on Wednesday added another line to his growing sporting CV when he was named the NBA Western Conference’s player of the month after helping the San Antonio Spurs win all 11 of their games in February.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8916d2cc-17de-11f1-acb4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/wembayama.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8916d2cc-17de-11f1-acb4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/wembayama.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">7dd1c08c-17db-11f1-91c0-d922d1bf4a90</guid><pubDate>Wed, 04 Mar 2026 16:02:46 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.rfi.fr/media/display/8916d2cc-17de-11f1-acb4-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/wembayama.jpg">Getty Images via AFP - JESSE D. GARRABRANT</source><dc:creator>Paul Myers</dc:creator></item></channel></rss>
